    "summary": "Repair contributor PR #99602 by rebasing/refitting the cron CLI rendering change onto current main, resolving the dirty merge state, preserving the existing behavior intent: human text output shows repeated error counts and cron show includes last error, while JSON/status machine fields remain canonical and undecorated.",
    "pr_title": "improve(cron): show consecutive failure count and last error in cron CLI output",
    "pr_body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nRepairs #99602 so the existing contributor change can land cleanly on current main. The user-facing behavior remains the same: cron list/show text output surfaces repeated error counts, cron show includes the last failure message, and machine-readable JSON/status values stay undecorated.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThe hydrated remediation inventory shows #99602 is focused and reviewed, but GitHub reports `mergeable=false` / `mergeable_state=dirty` at head `2e2a1f66d345dbfeaa606ebbb74b6d25cd771453`. Since maintainers can modify the branch, the narrow path is to repair that contributor branch instead of replacing the work.\n\n## User Impact\n\nOperators can distinguish a one-off cron failure from repeated failures and can see the most recent failure message in human CLI output without changing JSON automation contracts.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Source PR: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/99602 by @masatohoshino.\n- Hydrated checks for #99602 were broadly green before repair, including Real behavior proof, QA Smoke CI, build-artifacts, lint, prod types, test types, dependency guard, and security-fast.\n- Required after repair: `pnpm check:changed`; focused context: `pnpm test src/cli/cron-cli/shared.test.ts`.\n\nCredit: this repair carries forward @masatohoshino's original implementation and PR #99602.",
    "likely_files": [
      "src/cli/cron-cli/shared.ts",
      "src/cli/cron-cli/shared.test.ts"
    ],
    "validation_commands": [
      "pnpm check:changed",
      "pnpm test src/cli/cron-cli/shared.test.ts"
    ],
    "credit_notes": [
      "Repair contributor branch for #99602 rather than replacing it; preserve @masatohoshino's commits/attribution where the branch history allows.",
      "If the executor must squash or regenerate commits during conflict repair, the PR body and merge notes should retain credit for @masatohoshino and source PR https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/99602."
    ],
